.TH "ptep_force_prot" 9 "ptep_force_prot" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ptep_force_prot \- change access rights of a locked pte
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ptep_force_prot
.BI "(struct mm_struct *mm "  ","
.BI "unsigned long addr "  ","
.BI "pte_t *ptep "  ","
.BI "int prot "  ","
.BI "unsigned long bit "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mm" 12
pointer to the process mm_struct
.IP "addr" 12
virtual address in the guest address space
.IP "ptep" 12
pointer to the page table entry
.IP "prot" 12
indicates guest access rights: PROT_NONE, PROT_READ or PROT_WRITE
.IP "bit" 12
pgste bit to set (e.g. for notification)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if the access rights were changed and -EAGAIN if the current
and requested access rights are incompatible.
